{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":2995755,"name":"Tahbert","username":"TB273","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/f9ae1b/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-01-21T05:52:11.031Z","cooked":"

Hello!

Our team is currently looking to use the WCP Friction Brake on our GreyT Telescopes with the integrated gearboxes. However, the recommended piston (1 1/16" bore, 1/4" stroke, McMaster 1691T142) currently has a ship time of up to 6 weeks, which likely will be too late for us.

What alternative pistons are there that will work with the GreyT telescope gearbox? Right now I’m looking at McMaster 4208K145 (only difference seems to be that it is not specially labeled as impact resistance) and AutomationDirect’s C170025D (cheaper, but retracted/extended piston lengths are unknown).

Any help would be greatly appreciated!

The C170025D is a 1:1 replacement, that is the one we are using.

We switched to buying all of our cylinders from AD after realizing they were the same as the McMaster cylinders, just a different brand (Nitra vs Bimba) but at half the cost. They also have free 2 day shipping so it’s not much slower than McMaster shipping.
